title Electrical Energy Storage Landscape (April 2023)
style wardley

// Anchors — the scenario names "consumers" as the primary user need
anchor Consumers [0.98, 0.70]

// Top layer — what the consumer directly cares about
component Activity [0.90, 0.55]
component Control [0.85, 0.40]

// Generation & grid — the visible electricity services
component Electricity Generation [0.78, 0.72]
component Grid [0.74, 0.68]

// Grid models — two competing architectures
component Traditional Grid (Single-Machine View) [0.66, 0.62] inertia
component Distributed Grid (Fault-Tolerant, TCP/IP-style) [0.64, 0.32]

// Legacy control plane — the SCADA / AGC world
component Auto Generation Control (AGC) [0.58, 0.70]
component SCADA [0.56, 0.78] inertia
component Spinning Reserve [0.54, 0.72] inertia
component Fast-Response Systems [0.52, 0.38]

// Energy platform / integration layer
component Energy Platform [0.48, 0.30]
component Integration Layer (Pre-approval / Discovery) [0.44, 0.22]
component Adaptive Integration [0.42, 0.18]
component Plug-and-Play Integration [0.40, 0.28]

// Storage types
component Electrical Storage (Batteries) [0.36, 0.58]
component Hydro Storage (Pumped) [0.34, 0.82]
component Hydrogen Storage [0.32, 0.18]

// Supply chain underneath
component Sources [0.24, 0.70]
component Stockpile [0.20, 0.55]
component Material Supply Chain [0.14, 0.35]
component Supply Chain Awareness [0.12, 0.22]

// Dependencies — consumer chain
Consumers->Activity
Consumers->Control
Activity->Electricity Generation
Activity->Grid
Control->Grid
Control->Auto Generation Control (AGC)

// Grid depends on one of two models
Grid->Traditional Grid (Single-Machine View)
Grid->Distributed Grid (Fault-Tolerant, TCP/IP-style)
Electricity Generation->Grid

// Traditional control plane
Traditional Grid (Single-Machine View)->Auto Generation Control (AGC)
Traditional Grid (Single-Machine View)->SCADA
Auto Generation Control (AGC)->Spinning Reserve
Auto Generation Control (AGC)->SCADA

// Distributed model uses fast-response + platform
Distributed Grid (Fault-Tolerant, TCP/IP-style)->Fast-Response Systems
Distributed Grid (Fault-Tolerant, TCP/IP-style)->Energy Platform
Fast-Response Systems->Electrical Storage (Batteries)

// Platform / integration layer
Energy Platform->Integration Layer (Pre-approval / Discovery)
Integration Layer (Pre-approval / Discovery)->Adaptive Integration
Integration Layer (Pre-approval / Discovery)->Plug-and-Play Integration
Energy Platform->Electrical Storage (Batteries)
Energy Platform->Hydro Storage (Pumped)
Energy Platform->Hydrogen Storage

// Spinning reserve is standby generation — generation calls on it
Electricity Generation->Spinning Reserve
Electricity Generation->Hydro Storage (Pumped)

// Supply chain underneath storage
Electrical Storage (Batteries)->Sources
Electrical Storage (Batteries)->Material Supply Chain
Hydrogen Storage->Sources
Hydrogen Storage->Material Supply Chain
Hydro Storage (Pumped)->Sources
Sources->Stockpile
Sources->Material Supply Chain
Material Supply Chain->Supply Chain Awareness

// Evolution movements — scenario, not forecast
evolve Distributed Grid (Fault-Tolerant, TCP/IP-style) 0.55
evolve Fast-Response Systems 0.60
evolve Electrical Storage (Batteries) 0.72
evolve Hydrogen Storage 0.40
evolve Plug-and-Play Integration 0.50
evolve Material Supply Chain 0.45

// Strategic notes
note Distributed grid evolving faster than traditional control [0.68, 0.45]
note Material supply chain risk biting here [0.15, 0.30]
note Legacy AGC/SCADA inertia zone [0.55, 0.75]
